Defendant Remi S Williams in court with attorney Michael L. Chernin.  Sara Nicole Volden Schroeder appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Plea hearing proceeds.  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant sworn, examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  The Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon not to possess any firearms or body armor.    Court further advised defendant of voting ineligibility.    

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  The Court imposed the following sentence:
Defendant's TOTAL LENGTH OF SENTENCE shall be 4 years.  Defendant's TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin Prison System shall be for 2 years  with credit for 48 days time served.  Defendant shall serve 2 years on EXTENDED SUPERVISION.    The defendant IS  eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program, but not for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program.  The Court advised the defendant of his determinate sentence pursuant to statute and in accordance with Form CR-234.  Copy provided to defendant.  The Court STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed the defendant on probation to the State Department of Corrections for a period of three (3) years.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION (and Extended Supervision, if revoked):
 - Serve 54 days condition time at the House of Correction, STRAIGHT time; no good time;
 - No controlled substances or alcohol;
 - AODA assessment and treatment;
 - Urine screens;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Be given job and vocational training;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - No contact with B. A. M. (3/08/1997);
 - No contact with co-actor Corvelle Williams;
 - Pay the costs, surcharges and disbursements as ordered. Should defendant get revoked and be sent to prison, the Court ordered all sums to be paid from prison funds to be taken by the Department of Corrections and not to exceed 25%.  Balance to then be paid on Extended Supevision.   Failure to pay amounts in full would result in a civil judgment entered against defendant.

Filed,
Pretrial Incarceration Credit;
Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence;
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.
